      <header>

        <h2 class="node__title">
          <a href="/en/story/2024/05/1149191" rel="bookmark"><span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden">‘Our voices need to be included’: Trinidadian youth make case for strong role in climate negotiations</span>
</a>
        </h2>

        <div class="node__meta">
          
                      
            <div class="field field--name-field-news-date field--type-datetime field--label-hidden field__item"><time datetime="2024-05-04T12:00:00Z" class="datetime">4 May 2024</time>
</div>
      
                          
      <div class="field field--name-field-news-region field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__items">
              <div class="field__item"><a href="/en/news/region/americas" hreflang="en">Americas</a></div>
          </div>
  
                        
                    <p class="minimal-share"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://news.un.org/en/story/2024/05/1149191" title="Share this via Facebook" class="facebook" data-ms="facebook">Facebook</a>
<a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=‘Our voices need to be included’: Trinidadian youth make case for strong role in climate negotiations&amp;url=https://news.un.org/en/story/2024/05/1149191" title="Share this via Twitter" class="twitter" data-ms="twitter">Twitter</a>
</p>

        </div>

      </header>
      <div class="node__content clearfix">

        
        
            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-news-story-lead field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><p><span>Trinidad and Tobago is described as one of the “frontline States”, those nations that are most severely affected by the impact of the climate emergency, and youth activists are among the most prominent voices in the country calling for stronger action to combat the crisis, both at home and abroad.</span></p>
</div>
      
        

      </div>
