        <h2 class="node__title">
          <a href="/en/story/2024/04/1148966" rel="bookmark"><span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden">Polluting rivers, beaches and the ocean:  How can Trinidad solve its plastics problem?</span>
</a>
        </h2>

        <div class="node__meta">
          
                      
            <div class="field field--name-field-news-date field--type-datetime field--label-hidden field__item"><time datetime="2024-04-24T12:00:00Z" class="datetime">24 April 2024</time>
</div>
      
                          
      <div class="field field--name-field-news-region field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden field__items">
              <div class="field__item"><a href="/en/news/region/americas" hreflang="en">Americas</a></div>
          </div>
  
                        
                    <p class="minimal-share"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer.php?u=https://news.un.org/en/story/2024/04/1148966" title="Share this via Facebook" class="facebook" data-ms="facebook">Facebook</a>
<a href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Polluting rivers, beaches and the ocean:  How can Trinidad solve its plastics problem?&amp;url=https://news.un.org/en/story/2024/04/1148966" title="Share this via Twitter" class="twitter" data-ms="twitter">Twitter</a>
</p>

        </div>

      </header>
      <div class="node__content clearfix">

        
        
            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-news-story-lead field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><p><span lang="EN-GB">Plastic pollution blocks rivers, chokes oceans and makes its way into the food chain as microplastics. It’s a global environmental crisis, and small island developing States are especially vulnerable, having to cope with detritus washing up on their beaches, as well as the waste they generate themselves.&nbsp;</span></p>
