            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-news-story-lead field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><p>Climate change shocks caused record levels of disruption and misery for millions in Europe in 2023 with widespread flooding and severe heatwaves – a new normal which countries must adapt to as a priority, the <a href="https://eur02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwmo.us9.list-manage.com%2Ftrack%2Fclick%3Fu%3D618614864060486033e4590d6%26id%3Dce25bbabf9%26e%3De316a2b064&amp;data=05%7C02%7Cdaniel.johnson%40un.org%7Ca42e71fe442640d08b7908dc5d463701%7C0f9e35db544f4f60bdcc5ea416e6dc70%7C0%7C0%7C638487803378275862%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=BSIgOUFONAXEgx8o8GnE7fUHxCBEJLf9E%2BW0hAqh50U%3D&amp;reserved=0">UN weather agency said</a> on Monday.&nbsp;</p>
</div>
      
        

      </div>
      <footer>
        
        
        
      </footer>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>
</div>

    </div>
  
